history.origin: Denmark, Part 1 (1r-33v): 1514; Part 2 (48v:6-50v:6): s. XVI in.

layout.p: Written in long lines, 25-28 lines on each page. Rubrics and initials in red.

msItem.title: Leechbook

layout.p: Written in two columns, 30-31 lines per column.

handDesc.p: The script in the second part of the manuscript is smaller than in the first part, and it is slightly more cursive.

decoNote.p: Initials are colour-stroked with red ink.

history.origin: Written in Denmark in the beginning of the sixteenth century.
